article.headline: S. Illinois 65, St. Louis 56
article.story: CARBONDALE, Ill. (AP) -- Randal Falker scored 17 points and grabbed seven rebounds to lead Southern Illinois to a 65-56 victory Saturday over Saint Louis. Matt Shaw chipped in 13 points and seven rebounds for Southern Illinois (6-1), which led 31-25 at halftime and never trailed in the final 20 minutes. Saint Louis cut the lead to four in the second half, when a Tommie Liddell free throw made it 48-44 with 9:14 remaining. But Jamaal Tatum hit a jumper on the Salukis' next possession, triggering a 10-2 run over the next eight minutes that iced the game. Tatum finished with 11 points for Southern Illinois. The Billikens outshot Southern Illinois 47.5 percent to 38.9 percent, but were done in at the foul line, where they converted just 13 of 23 attempts for 56.5 percent. Southern Illinois made 17 of 20 foul shots, for 85 percent. Kevin Lisch and Liddell had 14 points apiece to lead St. Louis (5-2).
